  "response": "There could be several reasons for this feeling:\n\n1. Anxiety or paranoia\n- Potential underlying mental health concerns\n- Heightened sense of self-consciousness\n- Generalized anxiety disorder\n\n2. Psychological factors\n- Past experiences of feeling vulnerable\n- Trauma or personal history\n- Hypervigilance\n\n3. Environmental triggers\n- Crowded spaces\n- Unfamiliar surroundings\n- High-stress situations\n\n4. Physiological reasons\n- Stress hormones\n- Heightened sensory perception\n- Lack of sleep\n\n5. Actual situational awareness\n- People might genuinely be looking in your direction\n- Public spaces with high foot traffic\n\nRecommendations:\n- Consult a mental health professional if feeling persistent\n- Practice relaxation techniques\n- Build self-confidence\n- Consider cognitive behavioral therapy\n- Rule out any underlying anxiety disorders\n\nIf these feelings are intense or interfering with daily life, it's best to speak with a professional who can provide personalized guidance.",
